<H1>Philips Award Nomination Form</h1>

<P>
Nominations are invited for the Philips prize, which will be awarded
for the best recently published work over the past two or three years by a
young scientist (normally under the age of 35) in the field of Physical
Crystallography.  

<P> The award of &pound;250, which is sponsored by
Philips, will be made during the BCA Annual meeting in Easter each year.
 Nominations for the award should be sent <strong>
not later than 31st January 2000</strong> 
to the Chairman of the Physical Crystallography Group Committee: 

<P>
 <P>
        Prof J.L.Finney, F.Inst.P, FRSC,<BR>
        Department of Physics and Astronomy,<BR>
        University College London,<BR>
        Gower Street,<BR>
        LONDON WC1E 5BT<br>
<br>email: j.finney@ucl.ac.uk
 </p>

<P>
